definition: big/huge/large/major/great/wide/deep/older (than)/oldest/eldest/greatly/very much/(dialect) father/father's elder or younger brother

sentences.english: As more blood is forced in, the tiny cavern swells .
sentences.chinese: 當更多的血擠進來時，微小的蓄水池就脹大。

sentences.english: Methods to lower the swelling ratio are presented.
sentences.chinese: 最後提出了減小擠出脹大率的幾種方法。

sentences.english: Mournfully slowly they roll, silently swelling and mixing.
sentences.chinese: 這些雲悲哀地悠然舒捲着，無聲地脹大，又融合。

sentences.english: The effects of wall slip on co-extrusion flow field, interface shape and extrudate swell were discussed.
sentences.chinese: 主要介紹了黏彈流體擠出脹大的數值模擬研究進展。

sentences.english: The developments of investigations on extrudate swell by using numerical simulation methods are reviewed in this paper.
sentences.chinese: 主要介紹了黏彈流體擠出脹大的數值模擬研究進展。

sentences.english: The bellies of the starving children are swelling.
sentences.chinese: 飢餓的孩子們的腹部都脹大了。

definition: yellow face, emaciated body (idiom); malnourished and sickly in appearance
to feel sick/to feel nauseous/to feel disgusted
the spongy, white pulp inside the stem of rush plants, used as a wick for oil lamps
